CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1966, pg. 12A, reads: "Hail To The Champs - A happy Coach Willard Fisher of Schenley High School is surrounded by his jubilant players following last Saturday's thrilling victory against Chester for the state championship. Surrounding Fisher are Charley Burley, left, and Kenny Durrett.  Jake Williams is kneeling on the left and Ed Gibson is on the right. Marv Snowden is next to Durrett, while Jim Prince is on the left in the back row...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: State Basketball Champion Schenley High School players surrounding Coach Willard Fisher, including #24 Marvin Snowden, Edward "Petey" Gibson with towel around neck on right, and #54 Kenny Durrett, in Civic Arena
